{"id":18451,"title":"Admission prevalence and acquisition of nasal carriage of meticillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus (MRSA) in German rehabilitation centres.","abstract":"This prospective multi-centre study assessed nasal colonization with meticillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus (MRSA) among patients on admission to and discharge from 11 rehabilitation centres in Germany. On admission, 71 of 5896 patients (1.2%) carried MRSA. History of MRSA carriage [odds ratio (OR) 4.3, 95% confidence interval (CI) 1.8-10.6], hospitalization within the previous six months (OR 2.5, 95% CI 1.2-5.2), contact with pigs (OR 22.5, 95% CI 11.1-45.7) and presence of chronic wounds (OR 4.7, 95% CI 1.9-12.0) were independently associated with MRSA. On discharge, 0.3% of the patients had acquired MRSA. ","date":"2014-06-02","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24792577","annotations":[{"name":"Germany","weight":0.751464,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Germany"},{"name":"Pig","weight":0.265779,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pig"},{"name":"Confidence interval","weight":0.263198,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Confidence_interval"},{"name":"Staphylococcus aureus","weight":0.162801,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Staphylococcus_aureus"},{"name":"Chronic (medicine)","weight":0.141289,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chronic_(medicine)"},{"name":"Methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus","weight":0.0711346,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Methicillin-resistant_Staphylococcus_aureus"},{"name":"Prevalence","weight":0.0604488,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prevalence"},{"name":"Ratio","weight":0.0391252,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ratio"},{"name":"Colonization","weight":0.0377168,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colonization"},{"name":"History","weight":0.0370